Y
\operatorname{cov}(X,Y)=E[XY]-E[X]E[Y]
\operatorname{cov}(X,Y)
|\operatorname{cov}(X,Y)|^2=|E[XY]-E[X]E[Y]|^2=
\varrho(X,Y) := \frac{\text{cov}(X,Y)}{\sqrt{\text{var} X} \cdot \sqrt{\text{var} Y}}
\varrho(X,Y) \in [-1,1]
1 \geq |\varrho(X,Y)|^2 = \frac{\text{cov}(X,Y)^2}{\text{var} X \cdot \text{var} Y}
\text{var} X := \mathbb{E}((X-\mathbb{E}X)^2)
X
\text{cov}(X,Y)^2 \leq \text{var} X \cdot \text{var} Y
